%U A393968 6,0,2,5,8,1,8,0,0,0,9,3,0,2,4,3,9,8,5,9,3,1
%N A393968 Decimal expansion of Pi_5, a generalized version of Pi used in squigonometry.
%H A393968 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A393968/b393968.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A393968 Robert D. Poodiack, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.4169/math.mag.89.2.92">Squigonometry, Hyperellipses, and Supereggs</a>, Mathematics Magazine, vol. 89, no. 2, 2016, pp. 92-102.
%H A393968 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squigonometry">Squigonometry</a>.
%F A393968 Equals 2*Pi*sqrt(2 + 2/sqrt(5))*Gamma(6/5)/(Gamma(2/5)*Gamma(4/5)) (see Poodiack, 2016, eq. 8).
%F A393968 Equals 10*Gamma(6/5)^2/Gamma(2/5) = 10*A371856^2/A246745.
%F A393968 Equals 2*Integral_{t=0..1} 1/((1 - t^5)^(4/5)) dt.
%e A393968 3.800600555953746966012230617684211958045940397113...
%t A393968 First[RealDigits[10*Gamma[6/5]^2/Gamma[2/5], 10, 100]] (* or *)
%t A393968 First[RealDigits[2*Integrate[1/((1 - t^5)^(4/5)), {t, 0, 1}], 10, 100]]
%Y A393968 Cf. A393967 (Pi_3), A175576 (Pi_4).
